      "apple_rating": 0,
      "chunk_text": "This is a download from BBC Learning English.To find out more, visit our website.Hello, this is 6 Minute English from BBC Learning English.I'm Neil.And I'm Georgina.What type of books do you like to read, Georgina?I love reading crime fiction.You know detective stories by authors like Ruth Vendel or Agatha Christie.Really? Do you find them relaxing?",
      "embedding": [],
      "language": "zh",
      "created_at": "2025-07-10T14:45:13.933725",
      "source_model": "text-embedding-ada-002",
      "tags": "[\"ES\"]"
    },
    {
      "chunk_id": "a787c9a5-a151-4428-b406-f9237577f4bf",
      "chunk_index": 1,
      "episode_id": "6865015b66c1a4e8d11766f6",
      "podcast_id": "1304",
      "podcast_name": "",
      "author": "",
      "category": "",
      "episode_title": "The soothing power of books",
      "duration": "",
      "published_date": "",
      "apple_rating": 0,
      "chunk_text": "I wouldn't say relaxing exactly, but I get really involved in the story, trying to work out who the murderer is, then finding out on the last page.That's interesting, because today we'll be looking at how books can help us relax and feel more alive during troubled times.We'll be finding out how reading is one of the best ways to find relief from the pressures of modern life.Neil, are you talking about bibliotherapy?",
      "embedding": [],
      "language": "zh",
      "created_at": "2025-07-10T14:45:13.936264",
      "source_model": "text-embedding-ada-002",
      "tags": "[\"BI\", \"LED\", \"ES\"]"
    },
    {
      "chunk_id": "e4ad8c89-44aa-4b8e-9ae5-69dfd695837f",
      "chunk_index": 2,
      "episode_id": "6865015b66c1a4e8d11766f6",
      "podcast_id": "1304",
      "podcast_name": "",
      "author": "",
      "category": "",
      "episode_title": "The soothing power of books",
      "duration": "",
      "published_date": "",
      "apple_rating": 0,
      "chunk_text": "Exactly.Bibliotherapy is the prescription of books as a remedy to sickness.It's been around since 2013 when the UK charity Reading Agency published a list of books that doctors could offer to patients tackling topics from depression to dementia to chronic pain.",
      "embedding": [],
      "language": "zh",
      "created_at": "2025-07-10T14:45:13.938639",
      "source_model": "text-embedding-ada-002",
      "tags": "[\"BI\", \"ES\", \"AI\"]"
    },
    {
      "chunk_id": "e68b443f-bbd4-4fce-b0db-fe76400df292",
      "chunk_index": 3,
      "episode_id": "6865015b66c1a4e8d11766f6",
      "podcast_id": "1304",
      "podcast_name": "",
      "author": "",
      "category": "",
      "episode_title": "The soothing power of books",
      "duration": "",
      "published_date": "",
      "apple_rating": 0,
      "chunk_text": "Okay, well, we'll find out later if you are right.In bibliotherapy, people meet up to read together.",
      "embedding": [],
      "language": "zh",
      "created_at": "2025-07-10T14:45:13.940782",
      "source_model": "text-embedding-ada-002",
      "tags": "[\"BI\"]"
    },
    {
      "chunk_id": "679ddfe0-253c-42dd-bae1-c8be4437568f",
      "chunk_index": 4,
      "episode_id": "6865015b66c1a4e8d11766f6",
      "podcast_id": "1304",
      "podcast_name": "",
      "author": "",
      "category": "",
      "episode_title": "The soothing power of books",
      "duration": "",
      "published_date": "",
      "apple_rating": 0,
      "chunk_text": "Avis, who runs these reading groups, believes they help the participants come more alive.Here he is speaking to BBC Radio 4's You and Yours about what he's discovered.",
      "embedding": [],
      "language": "zh",
      "created_at": "2025-07-10T14:45:13.943009",
      "source_model": "text-embedding-ada-002",
      "tags": "[\"CI\", \"ES\"]"
    },
    {
      "chunk_id": "6607aaee-b83b-4c9e-9609-41cfe1a6af03",
      "chunk_index": 5,
      "episode_id": "6865015b66c1a4e8d11766f6",
      "podcast_id": "1304",
      "podcast_name": "",
      "author": "",
      "category": "",
      "episode_title": "The soothing power of books",
      "duration": "",
      "published_date": "",
      "apple_rating": 0,
      "chunk_text": "One type of reading is scanning, reading quickly in order to find specific information or skimming the page to get a general understanding.",
      "embedding": [],
      "language": "zh",
      "created_at": "2025-07-10T14:45:13.945280",
      "source_model": "text-embedding-ada-002",
      "tags": "[\"CI\", \"UI\"]"
    },
    {
      "chunk_id": "654a4096-3cbb-47d1-b905-e1522070c0e1",
      "chunk_index": 6,
      "episode_id": "6865015b66c1a4e8d11766f6",
      "podcast_id": "1304",
      "podcast_name": "",
      "author": "",
      "category": "",
      "episode_title": "The soothing power of books",
      "duration": "",
      "published_date": "",
      "apple_rating": 0,
      "chunk_text": "But the real therapy happens when a group reads literature – written work such as novels, poems or plays, which are thought to have artistic merit.When group members read literature, their brains get excited and start working from a different hemisphere – a word meaning half a sphere – usually half the earth, or in this case, the human brain.",
      "embedding": [],
      "language": "zh",
      "created_at": "2025-07-10T14:45:13.947918",
      "source_model": "text-embedding-ada-002",
      "tags": "[\"CI\", \"AI\"]"
    },
    {
      "chunk_id": "03340295-5bc6-49d5-8f9d-617fad883eb9",
      "chunk_index": 7,
      "episode_id": "6865015b66c1a4e8d11766f6",
      "podcast_id": "1304",
      "podcast_name": "",
      "author": "",
      "category": "",
      "episode_title": "The soothing power of books",
      "duration": "",
      "published_date": "",
      "apple_rating": 0,
      "chunk_text": "There are two methods, really.You can have ECG where you put electrodes on the scalp and it measures electricity so that you can have a print-off of a graph of the sudden leaps that can happen at particular moments in reading a poem or a play.",
      "embedding": [],
      "language": "zh",
      "created_at": "2025-07-10T14:45:13.950289",
      "source_model": "text-embedding-ada-002",
      "tags": "[\"CI\", \"ES\"]"
    },
    {
      "chunk_id": "8bafd773-d4b4-44a4-b57a-d35f983afdf0",
      "chunk_index": 8,
      "episode_id": "6865015b66c1a4e8d11766f6",
      "podcast_id": "1304",
      "podcast_name": "",
      "author": "",
      "category": "",
      "episode_title": "The soothing power of books",
      "duration": "",
      "published_date": "",
      "apple_rating": 0,
      "chunk_text": "The benefits of reading literature with others can be felt by group members as they begin to feel more alive and able to cope with life's ups and downs, but they can also be measured scientifically by recording brainwave activity.",
      "embedding": [],
      "language": "zh",
      "created_at": "2025-07-10T14:45:13.952662",
      "source_model": "text-embedding-ada-002",
      "tags": "[\"CI\", \"AI\"]"
    },
    {
      "chunk_id": "1f2fd02e-8ce6-4e37-8c14-743b1e588921",
      "chunk_index": 9,
      "episode_id": "6865015b66c1a4e8d11766f6",
      "podcast_id": "1304",
      "podcast_name": "",
      "author": "",
      "category": "",
      "episode_title": "The soothing power of books",
      "duration": "",
      "published_date": "",
      "apple_rating": 0,
      "chunk_text": "Brain activity is then measured by giving the reader a stimulus – something that encourages activity in people.In this case, it could be a poem or novel to read.Or something really stimulating, like a detective story.Or a work of literature, which reminds me of today's quiz question.I asked you to name the most popular book of all time and you said…",
      "embedding": [],
      "language": "zh",
      "created_at": "2025-07-10T14:45:13.955267",
      "source_model": "text-embedding-ada-002",
      "tags": "[\"UI\", \"ES\", \"AI\"]"
    },
    {
      "chunk_id": "cd7a6558-4f68-4ee9-81af-dabf5224044d",
      "chunk_index": 10,
      "episode_id": "6865015b66c1a4e8d11766f6",
      "podcast_id": "1304",
      "podcast_name": "",
      "author": "",
      "category": "",
      "episode_title": "The soothing power of books",
      "duration": "",
      "published_date": "",
      "apple_rating": 0,
      "chunk_text": "Today we've been discussing the therapeutic effects of meeting up with others in a reading group to read literature – writing of artistic value such as stories and poetry.",
      "embedding": [],
      "language": "zh",
      "created_at": "2025-07-10T14:45:13.957579",
      "source_model": "text-embedding-ada-002",
      "tags": "[\"EU\", \"ES\"]"
    },
    {
      "chunk_id": "57f3dcf4-dc60-42cd-b676-3cb5cee21888",
      "chunk_index": 11,
      "episode_id": "6865015b66c1a4e8d11766f6",
      "podcast_id": "1304",
      "podcast_name": "",
      "author": "",
      "category": "",
      "episode_title": "The soothing power of books",
      "duration": "",
      "published_date": "",
      "apple_rating": 0,
      "chunk_text": "All of which helps people dealing with trauma to come to life, feel active and more alive after a quiet period.",
      "embedding": [],
      "language": "zh",
      "created_at": "2025-07-10T14:45:13.959735",
      "source_model": "text-embedding-ada-002",
